data.description: Welcome Home to Drexel Hill, What do we have here.  ​A well-kept, pride of homeownership, twin property that is looking for a new homeowner. As you approach the property you will find the manicured front yard that is gleaming in curb appeal. This front lawn is ready for you to tap into the green thumb so you to plant your garden or beautiful flower bed.  As you enter the house you instantly feel right at home with the property's warm vibrant décor throughout. Next, the original hardwood flooring will capture your attention in the living room and dining room. The living room offers comforts for every season. So if you enjoy a flickering fireplace in winter months you will feel right at home here but if you prefer an autumn breeze then this home offers that to you as well with its large ceiling fan to give you ample ventilation when you do not want to run your central air conditioning. Next, the den can be your conversion room space that could be a bedroom, guestroom, office, playtime area, or your oasis to kick back and relax; or a place to watch, yell, or laugh at your favorite television program, the possibilities are endless. Since this home boasts of an abundance of windows and offers a wealth of natural light to all of the plant parents​ out there feel free to bring all of your tropical treasures to bloom and bask in this property's generous amount of sunlight.   Once you enter the kitchen you take notice of some of the vintage qualities that were preserved such as the built-in pantry and a landline telephone. The Deep under-mount sink is embossed with a gorgeous & sleek granite countertop featuring a gooseneck faucet. Are you ready to unleash the pastry chef inside of you? Well, I have news for you this house also offers a Samsung electric range. As many chefs will agree electric ranges are great for baking. But wait there’s more… The kitchen also features a food storage area that currently houses the new property owner’s deep freezer. Just after the kitchen storage area, you will find the property’s vibrant green grass and freshly painted deck in the backyard. Next, you will see the home’s one-car garage and smooth and leveled driveway. Don’t go just yet… As you venture back into the property head to the basement. You will discover the property’s powder bathroom and laundry area and yes the washer and dryer are included with the purchase of your new home. Now it’s time to venture upstairs and visit the sleeping quarters. Each of the 4 bedrooms offers plush freshly cleaned carpet and ample closet space to store your wardrobe. Two of the bedrooms offer ceiling fans so you can always enjoy a cool breeze no matter the temperature outside. Last but not least is the attic which features an unfinished space that is ready for a personal fitness area, game room, or any work-from-home business venture. No matter what you decide the attic is ready for you to create your dream or vision for the space. Are ready to say YES to this address? This house is ready for you to make it your NEW home.
